<%# src/views/partials/special-flash-option.ejs
    Issue #763 (the host surface for the #649 umbrella): the "Flash" option in
    the Special radio, plus the accordion panel that opens under it when it is
    picked.

    ONE partial, included by BOTH task-create-dialog.ejs (step 2) and
    task-edit-dialog.ejs — the same shape special-oneday-option.ejs already
    takes, so the create flow and the edit popup are the same control and
    cannot drift.

    The panel is shown by CSS alone
    (.special-option-group:has(.special-option input:checked)), not
    JavaScript — the same mechanism the worth chips, the Special radio and
    #755's day/bonus accordion already use. The `.special-option` scope in
    that selector is load-bearing: this panel's own Starts chips include an
    always-checked `flash_start_mode="now"` radio, and an unscoped
    `:has(input:checked)` would hold the whole accordion open from first
    paint regardless of which Special option is picked. The day+time
    sub-panel opens the same way, off the "Starts" chips.

    "Flash" is NOT a stored special_mode (src/services/tasks.js's MODES list
    deliberately excludes it — a flash reverts on its own when the window ends,
    which a stored enum cannot do). It rides the same radio group so the host
    sees one "what is special about this task" question, and the route reads
    the flash trio (flash_bonus / flash_minutes / flash_start_at) off the panel
    below.

    Locals:
      idPrefix   — 'task-create' | 'task-edit'; keeps element ids unique when
                   both dialogs are on the same page.
      eventDays  — REQUIRED, [{ iso, label }] from the #681 Configuration
                   page's wedding dates (src/routes/admin.js's GET
                   /admin/tasks render locals). No fallback, same as
                   special-oneday-option.ejs.

    The status strip's visibility has exactly ONE owner (issue #763 PR
    review, M3): src/routes/admin.js's GET /admin/tasks projection, where
    `flashStripLabel` is non-empty precisely when the task's flash state is
    `active` or `scheduled`. This include always renders the strip hidden —
    there is no per-state local to pass, because both callers (this file's
    two includes, in task-create-dialog.ejs and task-edit-dialog.ejs) render
    a shared, reusable dialog that cannot know in advance which task (if any)
    will be tapped next. admin-tasks.js's openEdit() is the only place that
    ever shows it, reading the tapped card's own data-flash-strip-label
    attribute and keying visibility off that string being non-empty — the
    same server-computed answer, read back rather than re-derived.
%>
<div class="special-option-group">
  <label class="special-option">
    <input type="radio" name="special_mode" value="flash" />
    <span class="special-option-face">
      <span class="special-option-title">Flash</span>
      <span class="special-option-sub">Worth extra for a few minutes — right now, or at a moment you pick</span>
    </span>
  </label>

  <div class="special-panel">
    <%# Always rendered (issue #763 plan step 6/7), never conditionally
        included — this dialog is shared across every card, so admin-
        tasks.js's openEdit() needs a real DOM node to toggle visibility on
        and fill per task, not markup that only exists for whichever state
        this particular server render happened to pass. Unconditionally
        hidden at first paint via an INLINE style, not the `hidden`
        attribute: theme.css's own `.flash-state-strip { display: flex }`
        rule (an author rule) would otherwise outrank the browser's
        low-priority `[hidden]` UA style — the same hazard theme.css already
        documents (and restates with `!important`) for `.guest-card[hidden]`
        — and an inline `style="display:none"` needs no accompanying
        `theme.css` change to win that fight, which matters because this
        screen's CSS is part of the owner-approved visual surface recorded in
        `.review_state/visual-approval/` (NOT the governance freeze, which
        covers no file under `src/`): an added rule there drifts the approval
        hash for a purely mechanical reason.
        admin-tasks.js's openEdit() uses the identical inline-style technique
        to show/hide and fill it per task, below. %>
    <div class="flash-state-strip" style="display:none">
      <span class="flash-state-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <span class="flash-state-text"></span>
      <input type="hidden" name="flash_cancel" value="" data-flash-cancel-input />
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-ghost flash-cancel-btn" data-flash-cancel>Cancel</button>
    </div>

    <div class="special-panel-field">
      <span class="field-label" id="<%= idPrefix %>-flash-bonus-label">Bonus while it&rsquo;s on</span>
      <div class="worth-chips" role="radiogroup" aria-labelledby="<%= idPrefix %>-flash-bonus-label">
        <% [1, 2, 3].forEach(function (n) { %>
          <label class="worth-chip">
            <input type="radio" name="flash_bonus" value="<%= n %>" />
            <span class="worth-chip-face">+<%= n %> pt<%= n === 1 ? '' : 's' %></span>
          </label>
        <% }); %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="special-panel-field">
      <label class="field-label" for="<%= idPrefix %>-flash-minutes">How long</label>
      <%# Thumb-sized minus/plus flanking the value, rather than the native
          number spinner's stacked arrows — those are a mouse control, and the
          host is on a phone in a reception hall. The field itself stays
          typable, so free entry (owner, 2026-07-20: "5 minutes and 2 hours are
          both valid") survives; the buttons are the fast path, not the only
          one. %>
      <div class="flash-minutes-row">
        <button type="button" class="flash-step-btn" data-flash-step="-5"
                aria-label="5 minutes less" aria-controls="<%= idPrefix %>-flash-minutes">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="22" height="22" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
            <rect x="4" y="11" width="16" height="2.5" rx="1.25" />
          </svg>
        </button>
        <span class="flash-minutes-value">
          <input type="number" class="flash-minutes-input" id="<%= idPrefix %>-flash-minutes"
                 name="flash_minutes" min="1" step="1" inputmode="numeric" placeholder="15" />
          <span class="flash-minutes-unit">minutes</span>
        </span>
        <button type="button" class="flash-step-btn" data-flash-step="5"
                aria-label="5 minutes more" aria-controls="<%= idPrefix %>-flash-minutes">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="22" height="22" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
            <rect x="4" y="11" width="16" height="2.5" rx="1.25" />
            <rect x="10.75" y="4.25" width="2.5" height="15.5" rx="1.25" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="special-panel-field flash-start-field">
      <span class="field-label" id="<%= idPrefix %>-flash-start-label">Starts</span>
      <div class="worth-chips" role="radiogroup" aria-labelledby="<%= idPrefix %>-flash-start-label">
        <label class="worth-chip">
          <input type="radio" name="flash_start_mode" value="now" checked />
          <span class="worth-chip-face">Now</span>
        </label>
        <label class="worth-chip">
          <input type="radio" name="flash_start_mode" value="later" />
          <span class="worth-chip-face">Pick a time</span>
        </label>
      </div>

      <div class="flash-when">
        <div class="day-chips" role="radiogroup" aria-label="Which day the flash starts">
          <% eventDays.forEach(function (d) { %>
            <label class="worth-chip day-chip">
              <input type="radio" name="flash_date" value="<%= d.iso %>" />
              <span class="worth-chip-face"><%= d.label %></span>
            </label>
          <% }); %>
        </div>
        <label class="flash-time-row" for="<%= idPrefix %>-flash-time">
          <span class="flash-time-label">at</span>
          <input type="time" class="flash-time-input" id="<%= idPrefix %>-flash-time" name="flash_time" />
        </label>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="special-panel-hint">
      While it&rsquo;s on, every guest who posts to this task earns the task&rsquo;s points
      plus this bonus. When the time runs out the task goes back to normal on its
      own &mdash; bonuses already earned stay earned.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
